\subsection{Statement of the main results}\label{sec:main result}
Let $\cX$ be a semi-projective toric Calabi-Yau 3-orbifold and $\bT\cong (\bC^*)^3$ be the algebraic 3-torus embedded in $\cX$ as a dense open subset. Let $\bT' \cong (\bC^*)^2$ be the Calabi-Yau $2$-subtorus of $\bT$ which acts trivially on the canonical bundle of $\cX$. (See Section \ref*{sect:Prelim} for more details.) In this paper, we prove the all genus mirror symmetry for the  $\bT'$-equivariant descendant Gromov-Witten theory of $\cX$. 

On the A-model side, consider the generating function of genus-$g$, $\bT'$-equivariant descendant Gromov-Witten invariants of $\cX$
$$
\llangle \frac{\gamma_1}{z_1-\hat{\psi}_1},\ldots, \frac{\gamma_n}{z_n-\hat{\psi}_n}\rrangle^{\cX,\bT'}_{g,n}
=\sum_{a_1,\ldots,a_n\in \bZ_{\geq 0}}
\llangle \gamma_1 \hat{\psi}^{a_1} ,\ldots, \gamma_n \hat{\psi}^{a_n} \rrangle^{\cX,\bT'}_{g,n}\prod_{j=1}^n z_j^{-a_j-1},
$$
